// Copy this file to Keyed.local.xcconfig and set CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY to
// an identity visible in `security find-identity -v -p codesigning`.
// Keyed.local.xcconfig is gitignored so each developer can sign with
// their own identity without affecting CI or release builds.
//
// Why: macOS TCC (Accessibility grants) keys off the app's Designated
// Requirement. With ad-hoc signing ("-") the DR pins to the cdhash,
// which changes on every rebuild — so macOS re-prompts for permission.
// Signing with a stable identity makes the DR reference the cert, and
// the grant sticks across rebuilds.
//
// Options, in order of preference:
//   1. A Developer ID Application cert (if you have one from Apple)
//   2. An Apple Development cert
//   3. A self-signed cert (Keychain Access → Certificate Assistant →
//      Create a Certificate → Self Signed Root → Code Signing). Note:
//      self-signed certs often don't show up in `security find-identity`
//      until you mark them "Always Trust" for code signing.

CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = Developer ID Application
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = BCB43KG62T
CODE_SIGN_STYLE = Manual
